The average monthly salary has increased by 9% in a year .
In the third quarter of 2018 , the average monthly nominal salary per employee amounted to 161.8 thousand tenge .
Nominal wages increased by 9.3% compared to the corresponding quarter of 2017 , real wages - by 3.1% .
The highest amount of remuneration was in financial and insurance activities - 317.4 thousand tenge , the lowest - in rural , forest and fisheries - 106.4 thousand tenge .
In the III quarter of 2018 , the number of employees in enterprises and organizations (excluding small enterprises engaged in entrepreneurial activity) amounted to 3.7 million people .
At the same time , the highest salaries were recorded in Atyrau region (310.5 thousand tenge), and the lowest - in Turkestan district (98.8 thousand tenge).
The 8th International Film Festival of Student Films &amp; quot; Bastau &amp; quot; has started in Almaty .
This year &amp; apos; s festival will be chaired by the famous director , screenwriter and teacher Irakli Kvirikadze .
The jury consists of Silvan Kutandin (" Letter to Stein "), Russian actress Elvira Bolgova (" My Armenian Wedding " , " Stepdaughter "), Kyrgyz director Temirbek Birnazarov and Kazakh Sabit Kurmanbekov .
In addition to the main jury, there is a jury consisting of young cinematographers-students.
This year the student jury includes students from Spain, Belarus, Kazakhstan, Kyrgyzstan and Russia.
Two years ago, the winner of the competition was the Spanish filmmaker Jago Mateo Velasco , this year he is the chairman of the jury of talented students .
