The most important thing is literacy, a new way of looking at the world, we want to open the way to the world of big festivals for unknown, young talents, - says Jago Mateo Velasco.
Honored guests of the festival were invited Dean of the Faculty of Film Production of Korea University of Media Arts Kim Yong-doo , sound director of Mosfilm Marina Nigmatullina and cinematographer and lecturer of the University of Karpenko-Karogo in Ukraine Yevgeny Filippov .
The jury and guests of the festival will hold creative meetings and master classes with Almaty students of cinematography and film professionals .
All events of the festival will be held at the National Academy of Arts named after T.Zhurgenov and Turan University .
The platform of the international film festival is important for young people.
From the very first job, a student should see what competition is like, not only what his classmates are shooting, but also how his peers in other countries are searching.
The participation of the film in the festival is one thing, but the exchange of ideas with the filmmakers is quite another.
Getting started is an essential step in creating a creative relationship.
Despite the difficulties, despite the difficulties of making a step into the big cinematography, cinema is developing.
Film festivals are very important for this purpose.
Film is a collective work, the international film language is universal, and we contribute to its development.
Here we not only watch films, but also learn how to make them , said Sergey Azimov , president of the festival .
According to the organizers , the festival of student films , which was interrupted in the Soviet period , continued in the period of independence and this year is held for the 7th time .
