Academic legacy - Astana Akshamy
Museum &amp; quot; Kitab &amp; quot; of the National Academic Library in Astana houses the manuscripts, library and personal belongings of the outstanding literary scholar, academician Zaki Akhmetov, including his writing desk.
These items were donated to the library by the wife of the academician Ziya Nasyrovna 4 years ago .
This year marks the 90th anniversary of the birth of Z. Akhmetov .
In this regard, the number of well-preserved monuments was replenished.
According to the head of the &amp; quot; Kitab &amp; quot; museum Moldir Baymakhanbetova , initially 43 folders with the scientist &amp; apos; s manuscripts were brought to the library .
Recently, another 67 folders were delivered.
The fund of the academic library has reached 850 books.
Among them there are books signed by teachers such as Mukhtar Auezov, Zhirmunsky, Malov, Manuilov, Nina Smirnova.
Zaki Akhmetov finished school at the age of 14 and graduated from KazMU at the age of 19 .
From 1947 to 1950 he studied at the graduate school of the Institute of Oriental Studies in Leningrad.
At the age of 27 he defended his thesis on "Lermontov and Abai".
Before the age of 40 he defended his dissertation on "The structure of Kazakh poetry" and received the degree of doctor of philological sciences.
Many of the works of the scientist remained in manuscript.
Some of his newspaper articles did not make it into the book.
Now the students intend to compile their works and publish 10 volumes , - said M. Baymakhanbetova.
