Starting from the new year, workers' wages will increase.
In his Address to the people of Kazakhstan , the Head of State instructed the Government to increase the minimum wage by 1.5 times from 28 thousand to 42 thousand tenge from January 1 , 2019 .
This directly affects the wages of 1 million 300 thousand people working in enterprises of various forms of ownership in all spheres .
In this regard , a meeting chaired by Governor of the region Berdibek Saparbayev was held in the regional administration .
We need to conduct accurate calculations in all enterprises, agricultural structures, other institutions, analyze the size of wages in different sectors of the economy and decide on the possibility of raising them.
The main thing is that every worker should feel the increase in his salary , as stated in the Address , - said the head of the region .
Head of the Department of Economy and Budget Planning of the region Gulkasima Suintayeva reported on the measures taken to increase the wages of low-paid workers in large and medium enterprises .
According to him , currently there are 278 small , medium and large private companies in the region , which employ 1046 people with salaries below 42500 tenge .
Most of them are in agriculture.
The average monthly salary of 464 people ranges from 33.3 thousand tenge to 49.3 thousand tenge .
In the construction industry, there are workers who receive similar salaries.
It is expected that from January 1 , the salaries of employees of these companies will increase from 27% to 56% .
A special working group has been created in the region to work on the issue of raising wages .
According to the Ministry of Labor and Social Protection of Population , 82 percent of 120.8 thousand employees in medium and small enterprises in the region have salaries below the average monthly wage .
About half of the employees of large enterprises are in this situation.
Starting from next year , 22 enterprises plan to increase the average salary of workers .
Among them, "Kazakoil" and "Stroybetonsnab" are going to raise the salaries of all workers by 10 percent.
The enterprises Aktobe Oil Complex and StroyDetail will follow the rate of 7 percent .
KazakhTurkMunay and Kazakhstan Oil Equipment Plant will increase wages by 5 percent .
Such positive trends will occur in the enterprises of &amp; quot; Caspiyneft &amp; quot; and &amp; quot; Transenergo &amp; quot; .
The total number of employees of these enterprises is 7.5 thousand people .
A total of 4,200 of them will receive an average salary increase of 7% from the new year .
Today , another 30 enterprises are considering raising wages .
The head of the region noted that the growth of wages will contribute to improving the welfare of the population and stressed the need to continue explanatory work with the leadership of enterprises .
At the meeting , heads of the regional industrial and innovative development , entrepreneurship , agriculture departments Yerlan Nazarov , Anar Darzhanova , Kusain Sarsembay and others reported on the work carried out in their areas .
At the end of the meeting , the head of the region said that the relevant authorities should take a responsible approach to the implementation of this issue , based on accurate analysis and clear reporting .
