Rules for the fight against "black archaeology" will be approved.
After the "black archaeologists", the monuments were left open and destroyed.
This was announced by the Minister of Culture and Sports Aristanbek Mukhamediuly during the presentation of the draft law &amp; quot; On protection and use of objects of historical and cultural heritage &amp; quot; in the Majilis .
The issue of regulation of archaeological and restoration works on objects of historical and cultural heritage requires revision .
It is no secret that our unique monuments or unexplored objects are often subjected to search and excavation by "black archaeologists", after which the monuments are left open and partially or completely destroyed.
In addition , there are cases when intensive construction works carried out in the territories adjacent to the objects of historical and cultural heritage have a significant impact on the historical integrity and preservation of monuments of history and culture , leading to negative consequences .
In general , there is a need to strengthen the tasks in the legal sphere , which require specific regulation and the creation of favorable conditions for the protection and use of objects of historical and cultural heritage , the minister concluded .
According to him , in this regard , at the legislative level , it is planned to establish a procedure for identifying and recording objects of historical and cultural heritage , as well as monitoring their condition , introducing qualitatively new mechanisms for preservation and use of objects of historical and cultural heritage in their original historical appearance .
In addition , it is proposed to establish rules and conditions for conducting archaeological works and combating " black archaeology " , regulate the legal regime of use of land plots in protection zones , construction of monuments of history and culture , determine the legal regime of use of natural landscape zones .
In the process of drafting the law , international experience was studied and taken into account .
For example, the Russian legislation includes measures to combat "black archaeology" for conducting illegal archaeological research, stealing archaeological objects, evading the transfer of artifacts to the state and others.
That is, criminal liability is provided.
In Italy, there are obligations for private collectors at the legislative level.
According to them , it is planned to create and periodically update lists of objects of culture and art of historical and artistic interest and private ownership .
At the same time , the objects owned by the owners of these objects , regardless of their nationality , citizenship , are subject to state protection , - said A.Mukhamediuly.
